In the first days of my youth I tried to And it in the creatures, as I saw
others do; but the more I sought, the less I found it, and the nearer I went
to it, the further off it was. For of every image that appeared to me, before
I had fully tested it. or abandoned myself to peace in it. an inner voice
said to me： ‘This is not what thou seekest.'
